  {
    "client_msg_id": "526c9842-9f84-4c34-9d77-c3c4aad76596",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "At around 52 minutes, he starts hammering on \"Conveyance\" and I almost did a spit-take. One of the ways I've been thinking about my current project is as a \"conveyance-oriented programming language\". Unfortunately (or thankfully?), the meaning of conveyance he's using is slightly different from the one I'm using, so I don't think they'll be any toe-stepping going on here.\n\nRegardless, this is an awesome talk.",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1534202350.000231",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
